            "summary":"You can never have too many dessert recipes, so give Mini Red Velvet Whoopie Pies a try. This recipe serves 1. For <b>$7.59 per serving</b>, this recipe <b>covers 55%</b> of your daily requirements of vitamins and minerals. One portion of this dish contains roughly <b>53g of protein</b>, <b>228g of fat</b>, and a total of <b>4543 calories</b>. It is brought to you by Foodista. 4 people have made this recipe and would make it again. <b>valentin day</b> will be even more special with this recipe. If you have marshmallow fluff, food coloring, baking soda, and a few other ingredients on hand, you can make it. From preparation to the plate, this recipe takes around <b>45 minutes</b>. With a spoonacular <b>score of 79%</b>, this dish is good. If you like this recipe, you might also like recipes such as <a href=\"https://spoonacular.com/recipes/mini-red-velvet-whoopie-pies-229749\">Mini Red Velvet Whoopie Pies</a>, <a href=\"https://spoonacular.com/recipes/red-velvet-whoopie-pies-1056354\">Red Velvet Whoopie Pies</a>, and <a href=\"https://spoonacular.com/recipes/red-velvet-whoopie-pies-527326\">Red Velvet Whoopie Pies</a>.",
